#!/bin/bash
# LoRA train script by @Akegarasu

# Train data path | 设置训练用模型、图片
pretrained_model="./sd-models/model.ckpt"     # base model path | 底模路径
is_v2_model=0                                 # SD2.0 model | SD2.0模型 2.0模型下 clip_skip 默认无效
parameterization=0                            # parameterization | 参数化 本参数需要和 V2 参数同步使用 实验性功能
train_data_dir="./train/1.formidable-default" # train dataset path | 训练数据集路径
reg_data_dir=""                               # directory for regularization images | 正则化数据集路径，默认不使用正则化图像。

# Network settings | 网络设置
network_module="networks.lora" # 在这里将会设置训练的网络种类，默认为 networks.lora 也就是 LoRA 训练。如果你想训练 LyCORIS（LoCon、LoHa） 等，则修改这个值为 lycoris.kohya
network_weights=""             # pretrained weights for LoRA network | 若需要从已有的 LoRA 模型上继续训练，请填写 LoRA 模型路径。
network_dim=32                 # network dim | 常用 4~128，不是越大越好
network_alpha=16               # network alpha | 常用与 network_dim 相同的值或者采用较小的值，如 network_dim的一半 防止下溢。默认值为 1，使用较小的 alpha 需要提升学习率。

# Train related params | 训练相关参数
resolution="768,768"  # image resolution w,h. 图片分辨率，宽,高。支持非正方形，但必须是 64 倍数。
batch_size=2          # batch size
max_train_epoches=20  # max train epoches | 最大训练 epoch
save_every_n_epochs=1 # save every n epochs | 每 N 个 epoch 保存一次

train_unet_only=0            # train U-Net only | 仅训练 U-Net，开启这个会牺牲效果大幅减少显存使用。6G显存可以开启
train_text_encoder_only=0    # train Text Encoder only | 仅训练 文本编码器
stop_text_encoder_training=0 # stop text encoder training | 在第N步时停止训练文本编码器

# 噪音
noise_offset="0" # noise offset | 在训练中添加噪声偏移来改良生成非常暗或者非常亮的图像，如果启用，推荐参数为0.1
keep_tokens=2    # keep heading N tokens when shuffling caption tokens | 在随机打乱 tokens 时，保留前 N 个不变。
min_snr_gamma=0  # minimum signal-to-noise ratio (SNR) value for gamma-ray | 伽马射线事件的最小信噪比（SNR）值  默认为 0

# 金字塔噪声
multires_noise_iterations=6 # 多分辨率（金字塔）噪声迭代次数 推荐 6-10。无法与 noise_offset 一同启用。
multires_noise_discount=0.3 # 多分辨率（金字塔）衰减率 推荐 0.3，须同时与上方参数 multires_noise_iterations 一同启用。

# Learning rate | 学习率
lr="3.5e-5"            # 3.5e-5=3.5*10^(-5)=0.000035
unet_lr="3.5e-5"       # 3.5e-5=3.5*10^(-5)=0.000035
text_encoder_lr="3e-6" #   3e-6=3.0*10^(-6)=0.000003
lr_scheduler="cosine_with_restarts" # "linear", "cosine", "cosine_with_restarts", "polynomial", "constant", "constant_with_warmup", "adafactor"
lr_warmup_steps=0                   # warmup steps | 学习率预热步数，lr_scheduler 为 constant 或 adafactor 时该值需要设为0。
lr_restart_cycles=1                 # cosine_with_restarts restart cycles | 余弦退火重启次数，仅在 lr_scheduler 为 cosine_with_restarts 时起效。

# Output settings | 输出设置
output_name="1.formidable-default" # output model name | 模型保存名称
save_model_as="safetensors"        # model save ext | 模型保存格式 ckpt, pt, safetensors

# Resume training state | 恢复训练设置
save_state=0 # save state | 保存训练状态 名称类似于 <output_name>-??????-state ?????? 表示 epoch 数
resume=""    # resume from state | 从某个状态文件夹中恢复训练 需配合上方参数同时使用 由于规范文件限制 epoch 数和全局步数不会保存 即使恢复时它们也从 1 开始 与 network_weights 的具体实现操作并不一致

# 其他设置
min_bucket_reso=256              # arb min resolution | arb 最小分辨率
max_bucket_reso=1024             # arb max resolution | arb 最大分辨率
persistent_data_loader_workers=0 # persistent dataloader workers | 容易爆内存，保留加载训练集的worker，减少每个 epoch 之间的停顿
clip_skip=2                      # clip skip | 玄学 一般用 2

# 优化器设置
optimizer_type="Lion" # Optimizer type | 优化器类型 默认为 AdamW8bit，可选：AdamW AdamW8bit Lion SGDNesterov SGDNesterov8bit DAdaptation AdaFactor

# LyCORIS 训练设置
algo="lora"  # LyCORIS network algo | LyCORIS 网络算法 可选 lora、loha、lokr、ia3、dylora。lora即为locon
conv_dim=4   # conv dim | 类似于 network_dim，推荐为 4
conv_alpha=4 # conv alpha | 类似于 network_alpha，可以采用与 conv_dim 一致或者更小的值
dropout="0"  # dropout | dropout 概率, 0 为不使用 dropout, 越大则 dropout 越多，推荐 0~0.5， LoHa/LoKr/(IA)^3暂时不支持

items.name: Kan'u Unchou (Ikkitousen)
items.description:
Lora model of Kan'u Unchou from Ikkitousen. Preview images done with weight 1.

This one is simple because it only has one outfit, but I still put an effort to make it work well. I had problem with hair and depending on prompt you may have to add low-tied long hair, hair over one eye to the prompt. Still depending on image model can struggle with hair shape making sense when it's not fully visible.

Other than that earring didn't really came out accurate, even after I retrained with just that in mind >_<

Full outfit prompt - kanu unchou, fingerless gloves, serafuku, midriff, loose socks, pleated skirt, yellow neckerchief, earrings, loafers

Additionally tags torn clothes, torn shirt, torn skirt, underboob work well.

Added 2fsVAE, it seems to me more suitable for the style of this model.

Not as faint as NAI VAE and not as overcontrasted as SD VAE.

It tends to lose details and have a bit of "ink bleeding", but nothing too crucial (IMHO) and looks like a good compromise overall.

items.name: Honda S2000
items.description:
https://t.me/stdif_kos

The Honda S2000 is a front-mid engine open top sports car that was manufactured by Japanese automobile manufacturer Honda, from 1999 until 2009. First shown as a concept car called the SSM at the Tokyo Motor Show in 1995, the production version was launched on April 15, 1999, to celebrate the company's 50th anniversary. The S2000 is named for its engine displacement of two litres, while "S" stood for "sports"[2] carrying on in the tradition of the S500, S600, and S800 roadsters of the 1960s.

S2000 logo

Several revisions were made throughout the car's production life, including changes to the engine, gearbox, suspension, interior and exterior. Officially two variants exist: the initial launch model was given the chassis code AP1; though cosmetically similar, the facelifted version, known as the AP2 in North America and Japan, incorporated significant changes to the drivetrain and suspension. Production of the S2000 ceased on August 19, 2009.

The Honda S2000 was notable for its exceptional specific power output of about 124 hp per litre, or about two horsepower per cubic inch, the highest of any mass production, naturally aspirated engined car.[3]

The S2000 has since become a legitimate modern classic car, having seen a significant appreciation in price for valued examples in good condition. In the JDM community and the car community as a whole, the most sought-after models are special edition productions such as the CR (Club Racer) in the USA market; the standard AP1 and AP2 models have achieved collectible status as well.

These are the new ControlNet 1.1 models required for the ControlNet extension, converted to Safetensor and "pruned" to extract the ControlNet neural network.

Also Note: There are associated .yaml files for each of these models now. Place them alongside the models in the models folder - making sure they have the same name as the models!

To be honest, there isn't much difference between these and the OG ControlNet V1's. These models are further trained ControlNet 1.0 models, with an additional 200 GPU hours on an A100 80G.

items.name: The Pale Man
items.description:
Del Toro has long been an inspiration to me since I first saw his 2006 masterpiece "Pans Labyrinth". A fantastic fusion of horror and fantasy, fully displaying his creative genius and unrivalled to this day. As a tribute to his work, I decided to take his freakiest creation, "The Pale Man" and try to capture its entirety in dreambooth. Built on 55 images taken from a lifesize model, a lifesize bust and some denoised screenshots. Trained at 768 resolution for 5k steps with 2k class images.

I don't expect a lot of interest in this sort of freakish model but, I will be happy to see it reach even just a few like minded fans of fantasy macabre and thought it was worth sharing here.

I've spent countless hours optimising my workflow for this type of full figure checkpoint in dreambooth and I have quite a few models I will now start releasing on a weekly basis.

items.name: Falkons (Anime and Hentai)
items.description:
Preface: no trigger words and ready-to-go example

This model has no trigger words and doesn't require any other content, but I highly suggest to use negative prompts, at least EasyNegative and bad_prompt_version2, which let you refine your creations, I am going to leave an example on how to use them and the download link for both of them.

Ready-to-Go Example:

masterpiece, portrait of 1girl,
Negative prompt: (worst quality, low quality:1.4), watermark,
Steps: 20, Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras, CFG scale: 7, Seed: 3209849427, Size: 540x960, Model hash: b6e7035f54, Model: falkonsAnimeAndHentai_v13, Denoising strength: 0.1, Hires upscale: 2, Hires steps: 20, Hires upscaler: R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B, Version: v1.3.2

Introduction

In the world of anime, style and aesthetics play a huge role in creating memorable and captivating characters. From bold and vibrant colors to intricate and detailed designs, there's no limit to the creativity that can be expressed through anime. In this model, we embrace the anime style and bring it to life with our own unique spin. Each character is carefully crafted to embody the essence of the anime universe, with exaggerated features and dynamic poses that capture the imagination. So if you're looking for a model that truly captures the spirit of anime, look no further than our collection.

How to install

  1. Download and install Stable Diffusion, I personally suggest the executable version by AUTOMATIC1111.

  2. Download Falkons model in .safetensor format and insert it into the "ckpt" folder.

  3. Start Stable Diffusion.

  4. Select the "Falkons.safetensor" model from the "Stable Diffusion checkpoint" dropdown menu.

Install add-ons and plug-ins: LORA, Textual Inversion, Extensions

This model is compatible with LORAs, Textual Inversion embeddings and Stable Diffusion's extensions, just download your favourites and put them rispectively in stable-diffusion-webui/models/Lora, stable-diffusion-webui/embeddings and stable-diffusion-webui/extensions.

Each add-on has its own trigger words or tags to be added in prompt in order to be triggered. In Stable Diffusion Web UI, you can click on the "show/hide extra networks" button, right below the Generate button, here you can click on Refresh, then on Textual Inversion tab or Lora tab, finally you can click on your wanted add-on to automatically add the trigger words or tags.

I highly suggest EasyNegative and bad-hands-5, download EasyNegative.safetensor and bad-hands-5.pt from https://huggingface.co/datasets/gsdf/EasyNegative and https://huggingface.co/yesyeahvh/bad-hands-5/, copy them in stable-diffusion-webui/embeddings, and use the words EasyNegative, bad-hands-5 as negative prompt to trigger them.

How to use

Of course you can try it with the prompt, sampling methods, steps, CFG, etc. you desire, I use to generate images with:

  • Sampling methods: Euler a, DPM++ SDE Karras or DDIM

    • DPM++ SDE Karras for overall best results with characters

    • Euler a for a more classic toon effect or DDIM for faster generation, both still offer good quality, but these samplers tend to generate deformed hands

  • Sampling steps: I usually set a minimum of 20 steps, more steps often help to generate a more detailed image, but it's not always true, and typically there is less difference as the number of steps increases

  • Restore faces, Tiling and Hires. fix turned off

  • Dimensions: I suggest you to choose multiple of 64. I usually pick 640x960, but I have noticed good results with other resolutions such as 512x512, 512x704, 512x960, 624x1176, 720x1024, 960x1280, while I have experienced poor results with bigger resolutions you can still generate low-resolution images first, then use stable diffusion img2img to increase their resolution through upscaling techniques, e.g. you can generate a 640x960 picture and then upscale it to 1280x1920, increasing both quality and details; I will update this readme with more details later

  • Batch size and batch count: my GPU can handle a Batch size of 5, which means 5 images generated per run at once, it really depends on your GPU's VRAM, so find the highest number of batch size you can handle. With batch count, Stable Diffusion starts a new run automatically after the previous one, so you get the multiplication result of the two numbers (e.g. batch size: 5, and batch count: 10, means 50 output images)

Examples

Example 1

You can start with very easy prompt, such as:

Prompt: a girl,
Negative prompt: (worst quality, low quality:1.4), watermark,
Steps: 20, Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras, CFG scale: 7, Seed: 2118282899, Size: 640x960, Model hash: 460b71c1c2, Model: Falkons

Example 2

You can try something more detailed (for example if you want to generate the same character in different poses or in different outfits):

Prompt: masterpiece, best quality, best resolution, girl, perfect anatomy, tight, fantasy worlds background, fantasy, determined, power, flames, intense, night sky, outdoors, moon, stars, clouds, wind, trees, night, sorceress, witch, profession witch, witch uniform, summoning, glowing runes, neck ribbon, hair ornament, heart jewelry crystal, lace feather white frills, gloves, thighhighs, skirt, thighboots, neckline, extrovert personality, favourite color blue, blue eyes, blue hair, short hair, large breasts, small waist, shiny skin, looking at viewer, magic circle, standing in the center of the circle,

Negative prompt: worst quality, low quality, EasyNegative, comic, sketch, not masterpiece, not best quality, not best resolution, poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, sketches, mutated, mutilated, monochrome, grayscale, greyscale, logo, watermark, duplicate, artifact, noise, film grain, blur, blurry, deformed, distorted, disfigured, fused fingers, extra fingers, twisted, malformed hands, ((((mutated hands and fingers)))), deep depth of field, simple background, abstract background,

Steps: 20, Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras, CFG scale: 7, Seed: 648403476, Size: 640x960, Model hash: 3624a75e34, Model: Falkons

License

You can use this template for commercial purposes but not solding it directly.

Please mention you have used the Falkons model to spread the word! Thank you!

items.name: Voicemod protogen + protogen furry
items.description:
The voicemod protogen, trained using the dreambooth extension for Automatic1111 webui. it was trained on only 5 images of the voicemod protogen, combined with 10 images of generic protogens, all simply tagged to get the model to understand more concepts that can apply to protogens.

I had previously attempted it with just the 5 images I have of the character, this caused it to lack knowledge of features that are common with protogens, and made it home towards generating images that look like copies of the training data. That's why I included the 10 extra images. And it worked great!

This is the first LoRA I am publishing, after playing around with LoRAs for a bit I think this one is good enough to publish.

training

The LoRA was trained using the dreambooth extension for Automatic1111 webui. I used 15 images of protogens, of which 5 were of the voicemod protogen specifically. I used deepbooru to caption the images, then edited the captions to use spaces instead of underscores, and added more specific information, removed incorrect tags.

I generated 75 classifier images. And just let the LoRA train for 2 hours.

For the base model I trained it on was a 50/50 merge of AbyssOrangeMix3 and Anything v4.5. However, the LoRA should work fine on most models.

how to use:

main trigger word: "voicemod protogen"

additional trigger words: "striped thighhighs", "striped arm warmers", "[color] visor", "multicolored fur"/"multicolored hair", "[facial expression] expression"

recommended to have in negative prompt: "text", "speech bubble", "watermark"

known limitations:

  • unable to generate 3d protogens, the training data was almost exclusively 2d and it seems it has associated the character to be in 2d, using it on a model that usually generates 3d content will most likely cause it to generate the character in 2d.

  • changing the visor color will change the main theme color of the protogen as well, and it might be inconsistent too.

note

the model is capable of generating different protogens, however you will still need to specify "voicemod protogen", just putting "protogen" often works but has issues with the visor. instead, specify "voicemod protoen" and specify the other details you want changed.

items.name: Narwhal (Kemono Friends)
items.description:
动物朋友/兽娘动物园的角色一角鲸。模型基于同人图训练。底模使用anythingV5Anything_anythingV5Prt，在站内搜索anything v5可以找到。

这个模型并没有达到我的全部预期，但关键的角色特征已经足够还原。再进一步训练会用掉我太多时间，如果没有需求我可能不会继续更新了。

我首先训练了一角鲸的基础特征，然后再进一步训练她的头鳍、尾巴和两套衣服。不幸的是她的武器和尾巴的效果很不理想，相对的你可以把它们放在negative prompt里。

有时候尾巴会被错误地识别为头发的一部分，你可以尝试删掉 short_hair_with_long_locks

可用的角色特征tag（不想要尾巴时 cetacean_tail 也要加入negative prompt）：

narwhal_(kemono_friends), narwhal_weapon, narwhal_tail,

头发和眼睛：

narwhal_fins, short_hair_with_long_locks, side_ponytail, short_hair, multicolored_hair, grey_hair, black_hair, white_hair, blue_eyes,

默认装扮：

narwhal_Default, sailor_dress, sailor_collar, black_choker, puffy_short_sleeves, bow, frilled_dress, white_dress, frills, black_hair_bow,

个性装：

narwhal_Personal_Fashion, hat, bow, coat, long_sleeves, high_collar, red_skirt, pleated_skirt, plaid_skirt, frilled_skirt, black_thighhighs, boots, red_hair_bow,

tag不是必要的，但是也许能让角色特征更加稳定。你可以选择性地使用这些tag。

Translated by Google:

Narwhal, a character from Kemono Friends. The model is trained on fanart. The training model uses anythingV5Anything_anythingV5Prt, you can find it by searching for anything v5 in the site.

The model didn't live up to all my expectations, but the key character traits were restored enough. Further training will take up too much of my time, and I may not continue to update if there is no demand.

I first trained the basic features of the narwhal, and then went further to train her head fin, tail, and two suits of clothing. Unfortunately her weapon and tail don't be restored very well, instead you can put them in a negative prompt.

Sometimes tails are misidentified as part of hair, you can try removing short_hair_with_long_locks

items.name: Change-A-Character: Symbiote Taking Over Your Waifu!
items.description:
Note #1: This is a Locon. Install the extension to get it to work. I've found them to do better when working on ideas that I want easily added to one of my LORA characters. Also, they're WAY less damaging to images, even at high weights.

What does it do you ask? Part of my CAC series, this one focuses on a symbiote taking over and infecting your waifu. It has a couple different trigger words that have various effects, as well as some recommended general tags if you want to emphasize certain aspects that I have found fun. I didn't hard bake them into the Locon but let them be easily called. Please read the next section for information.

How to use it: First we have the core triggers baked into the Locon.

TOver - Main trigger word.

NOMASK or WMASK - Choosing one of these tries to get the Locon to emphasize mask or not.

Optional but tags that are powerful in here:

mask, skin tight, bodysuit, slime (substance), covered eyes, no eyes, monster girl, tentacles, torn clothes - All these tags have a powerful effect in this Locon and work well thematically. Pick and choose which ones (if any) you want to use in a given picture. There are definitely a lot of other tags to use though, just some recommendations!

Extra, Extra!: Should be well trained and usable in most models. Images shown for example.

Picture Descriptions:

1-3: AnythingV3 using just this Lora with simpler prompts.

4: AnythingV3 combo'd with my released Amiri (Iruma-Kun) Lora.

5: AnythingV3 combo'd with my released Rozalin (Disgaea 5) Lora.

6: AnythingV3 combo'd with my released Catherine (Catherine Full Body video game) Lora and with the mask on.

7: AnythingV3 combo'd with my in progress Pet Play Locon.

8: AnythingV3 combo'd with my in progress Knight-ify Locon..

9: AbyssOrange with just this Lora.

10: PerfectWorld using just this Lora.

How was it trained?

It was trained on animefull_final with 27 images with the usual self-pruning and tagging and a wide range of different images. I like keeping my prompts simple for the first few pictures so that you can see it without a whole bunch of mumbo jumbo. Make your pictures better than mine though!

What's next for this?

Hopefully this one is better, if not I'll update it again.

What's next that isn't this?

More character Loras. (Zephia Fire Emblem Engage, Ivy from Soul Calibur 5, Heine from Combatants Will Be Dispatched, Conqueror Lilias from E7, Evelynn from LoL (both base and All Out version), Tharja from Fire Emblem, Catherine from Catherine Full Body, Miku from Idaten Deities, Kuribayashi Shino from GATE, Rin Sohma from Fruits Basket, Kasumi from P5, Ann from P5, Ikumi Mito from Food Wars, Alice Nakiri from Food Wars, Chika Fujiwara from Kaguya-sama, Lulu from FF10, Momo from My Hero, Sheik from Zelda, Vivy from Vivy, Lucoa and Tohru from Dragon Maid, Dominique de Sade from Vanitas, and Dos from One Punch Man.) And maybe Wilhelm van Astrea, my favorite Re:Zero husbando or a Prinny from Disgaea.

V2's of some of the previous Loras. Specifically make them more diversely acceptable with other models and LORA's.

I also have some more quite NSFW Locon's. I decided to list them as well, so if people have preferences on which to fix up first let me know. Specifically, Demonic Transformation, being stepped on, Robotification, Petrified (I'm unsure if I should bother with this one anymore), Infection (this one is VERY nsfw, as the waifu is completely infected), Dominatrix (waifu becoming a dominatrix), Brainwashing Machine, Tentacles, Pillory, Masked Evil (A mask that possess' the waifu), Latex Corruption, Combat Drone (hard to describe but basically making them a mindless sci-fi combat warrior), JAV Supervillain, Jiangshi (Transforms into a Jiangshi), Mind Flayer Defeat, Blacked, Harem Outfits, Hourglass Figure (just to make your waifu curvy), and Holding a Leash.

And, uh, I want to make a few "normal" Locon's so I have an "knight-ify" your character one coming up. And a forest fairy one as well. And a officer one. And a barbarian one.

Additionally, I love the style of Defaultz_17, so I'm making a Locon to mirror that.

Or just give me some random suggestion or priority opinions. That works too.

items.description:
Lora trained on Pyrrha Nikos from rwby

Master model 2,5D: ReV Animated (mostly used), OrangeChillMix (this one is also more realistic)

anime: DivineEleganceMix

i also used epi_noiseoffset with 0,7 weight

negative embeddings: embedding:bad-hands-5, embedding:ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, embedding:bad-artist, embedding:EasyNegative

postive promt for most of the colosseum pictures: ((best quality)), ((masterpiece)), ((realistic)), (detailed), (1 girl) women, pyrrha nikos a woman with long red hair wearing a brown corset and armor holding a spear and a shield, green eyes, full body, looking at viewer, solo, detailed background, (tribal background:1.2), colosseum, closed mouth, absurdres

postive promt for most of the Indoor pictures: ((best quality)), ((masterpiece)), ((realistic)), (detailed), (1 girl) women, pyrrha nikos a woman with long red hair wearing a brown corset, green eyes, looking at viewer, solo, upper body, detailed background, Ornate, Indoor, (Renaissance:1.2), (Vintage Windows:1.1), Royal Furniture, close up, closed mouth, absurdres

also try to keep this in mind if using ReV Animated:

  • Order matters - words near the front of your prompt are weighted more heavily than the things in the back of your prompt.

  • Prompt order - content type > description > style > composition

  • This model likes: ((best quality)), ((masterpiece)), (detailed) in beginning of prompt if you want anime-2.5D type

  • This model does great on PORTRAITS

Recommended settings:

  • Make sure you are aware on the usage instructions of LORA

  • VAE: orangemix.vae.pt (for 2,5D pictures), vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (for realistic models), pastel-waifu-diffusion.vae.pt and blessed2.vae.pt (for anime models)

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras or DPM++ 2M Karras

  • Steps: 20 to 35

  • Clipskip: 1 or 2

  • Upscaler : img2img in comfyui using 4x-UltraMix_Smooth

  • CFG Scale : 5 to 9 (mostly 7 and 8)

  • LORA weight for txt2img: 0.5-1 (for the examples i mostly used 0.8)

  • Denoise strength for img2img: 0.4 to 0.7

Trained with ReV Animated checkpoint

for the pictures i used comfyui

follow me on Instagram, Youtube and my website.

QAnon Shaman

Suggested Weight: 0.6-1.2 (this is where the embedding shines imo, you can dial it up or down as much as you need, depending on how well it's mixing with the other subject)

Suggested prompts

  • portrait photo of (man:1.0) as (q4n0n5h4m4n:0.9), horns, facepaint

  • portrait photo of (man:1.0) as (female q4n0n5h4m4n:0.9), horns, facepaint

  • portrait photo of (man:1.0) as (q4n0n5h4m4n:0.9), horns:0.3, facepaint:0.6

To give someone horns, you usually need to add horns to the prompt, which depending on the subject and rest of the prompt might need to be weighted up or down (too high will turn them into a goat, too low won't render horns at all).

Also facepaint can be most specific like patriotic facepaint

Training

  • trained on ~12 images

  • Learning Rate: 0.005:1000, 0.001:2000, 0.0001:5000, 0.00005

  • Batch Size: 1

  • Gradient Steps: 1

items.description:
My 4th try at it and i wont probably try this anymore, this was done on Hollowstrawberry's lora trainer: https://colab.research.google.com/github/hollowstrawberry/kohya-colab/blob/main/Lora_Trainer.ipynb

Trained with 61 images at 768 resolution for 5 repeats and 10 epochs, used flip_aug and min_snr_ganma, 2e-4 unet/1e-4 text econder lr, batch size 2.

Getting waai fu right is a nightmare and i think part of the problem is the models not being good at it, i only tested with 7thanimev3c: https://huggingface.co/syaimu/7th_Layer/blob/main/7th_anime_v3/7th_anime_v3_C.safetensors but if someone has a merge with a furry model and it looks better on those please do tell me.

More ammount of time went into pruning this time around, i decided to swap 1girl for furry female since leaving it before was detrimental, other than that the minimum tags to prompt her are "waai fu, furry female, tiger ears, body fur", if you want her glasses add "orange-tinted eyewear, round eyewear" and for her default outfir use "default china dress, capelet, pelvic curtain, elbow gloves, orange belts", add or remove "animal nose" to positive/negative prompts depending on what you want. Additionally you can use tiger girl, tiger tail to help prompt the tail but expect random tails around and tail limbs, i honestly dunno how to fix those.

Other than that here is the tag frequency for anyone interested: https://files.catbox.moe/0a76lr.txt

items.name: SR-Omega
items.description:
SR-Omega is a merge of a few handpicked checkpoints/mixes which aims to help generate semi-realistic images.

This was supposed to be an update to SR-Alpha, but the style of this merge's outputs was way too different to be classified as such, as, in my opinion, the images generated with this merge have drastically more realistic proportions compared to the older model.

This merge is a combination of the following models/mixes below:

V1:

  • 🌟M4RV3LS & DUNGEONS v1.0🌟

  • DuelAnimeMix

  • Deliberate

V2:

  • 🌟M4RV3LS & DUNGEONS v1.0🌟

  • dalcefo_v5

  • Deliberate

V3 and V4:

  • M4RV3LS & DUNGEONS v2.0

  • Comics_Vision

  • Deliberate

V5:

  • M4RV3LS & DUNGEONS v2.0

  • Level4 - v5.0 NO VAE

  • BlueberryMix

  • Deliberate

I highly recommend inpainting for best results and to unlock the full potential of the merge. Separate inpainting model not required. Face restore (GFPGAN) has been used to just bring out a bit of realism to the outputs. Codeformer seems to do fine, but it interferes with the styling of the output and overpowers some of the facial details embedded in prompts too much even at balanced weights.

Recommended Settings:

  • Sampling Method: DPM++ 2M Karras, DPM++ 2S a Karras, or Euler A

  • Sampling Steps: 30

  • CFG = 7-10

  • Denoising Strength = 0.3-0.5 (img2img/inpainting)

*I only use denoising strength values greater than 0.4 if I want to drastically change the appearance of a particular feature/region of the image. I mainly use this if I want to fix hands that seem to be too deformed to be saved with lower denoising strength values.

Suggested Embeddings:

  • https://civitai.com/models/17083/bad-picture-negative-embedding-for-chilloutmix

  • https://civitai.com/models/11772/verybadimagenegative

  • https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1032948846197747731/1069660323709190195/bad-hands-5.pt

  • Deep Negative V1.x - V1 75T | Stable Diffusion Textual Inversion | Civitai

  • Bad artist Negative embedding - Bad artist | Stable Diffusion Textual Inversion | Civitai

VAE:

  • NoCrypt/blessed_vae · Hugging Face

Credits to the respective original creators of the resources used.
